# Hebrew RTL Support

## Configuration

- **Root Layout**: [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) sets `lang="he"` and `dir="rtl"`
- **Metadata**: Hebrew title and description in layout
- **CSS**: RTL-aware styling with Tailwind CSS

## RTL Best Practices

### Layout Considerations

- Use `dir="rtl"` on HTML element
- Consider RTL when positioning elements (left/right margins, padding)
- Test layouts in both LTR and RTL modes
- Use logical properties when possible (`margin-inline-start` vs `margin-left`)

### Text and Content

- Set `lang="he"` for Hebrew content
- Use proper Hebrew fonts and typography
- Consider text direction in UI components
- Test with Hebrew placeholder text

### Component Development

```typescript
// RTL-aware component example
export default function RTLComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="text-right rtl:text-right ltr:text-left">
      {/* Hebrew content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### CSS Classes

- Use Tailwind's RTL utilities: `rtl:` and `ltr:` prefixes
- Consider using logical properties in custom CSS
- Test spacing and alignment in RTL mode

## Testing RTL

- Always test components with Hebrew text
- Verify layout works correctly in RTL mode
- Check form inputs and interactive elements
- Ensure proper text alignment and spacing